   "source": [
    "<h1 style=\"color: #96174e\">Using LLMs to Compare Multiple Drafts of the Same Idea</h1>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>In this post, I examined how an LLM can be used to generate and compare multiple drafts of the same idea. This is especially useful during revision, when it can be hard to see alternative ways of expressing the same point.</p>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>Rather than choosing the first output the model produced, I intentionally asked for multiple versions to compare tone, clarity, and emphasis.</p>\n",
    "\n",
    "<h4 style=\"color:#0707ff\">The Graphic</h4>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>\n",
    "<img src=\"drafts.png\" alt=\"Comparing multiple writing drafts generated by an LLM\" width=\"60%\">\n",
    "</p>\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "<h4 style=\"color:#0707ff\">Original Idea</h4>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p style=\"background-color: #f8f8f8; padding: 10px; border-radius: 8px;\">\n",
    "LLMs can support writing, but they work best when users remain actively involved in shaping and revising the output.\n",
    "</p>\n",
    "\n",
    "<h4 style=\"color:#0707ff\">Prompt</h4>\n",
    "\n",
    "<div style=\"background-color: #f8f8f8; padding: 10px; border-radius: 8px;\">\n",
    "<blockquote>\n",
    "Write two different versions of this idea, each with a slightly different emphasis.\n",
    "</blockquote>\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "<h4 style=\"color:#0707ff\">Response 1</h4>\n",
    "\n",
    "<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 10px; border-radius: 8px;\">\n",
    "<blockquote>\n",
    "Large language models can be helpful writing tools, but their value depends on users actively revising and shaping the generated content rather than accepting it as-is.\n",
    "</blockquote>\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>This version emphasized responsibility and caution, framing the LLM as a tool that requires oversight.</p>\n",
    "\n",
    "<h4 style=\"color:#0707ff\">Response 2</h4>\n",
    "\n",
    "<div style=\"background-color: #f0f8ff; padding: 10px; border-radius: 8px;\">\n",
    "<blockquote>\n",
    "When used thoughtfully, LLMs can support the writing process by offering drafts that users refine, adapt, and improve through active engagement.\n",
    "</blockquote>\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>This version felt more optimistic and process-oriented, highlighting collaboration between the writer and the model.</p>\n",
    "\n",
    "<h1 style=\"color: #96174e\">Reflection</h1>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>This experiment showed that generating multiple drafts can reveal subtle differences in emphasis that are easy to miss when working with a single version.</p>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>For blogging, this makes revision feel more exploratory rather than corrective. Comparing drafts helps clarify what I actually want to say, not just how to say it.</p>\n",
    "\n",
    "<p>Overall, this use case reinforced that LLMs are most valuable when they expand the space of possibilities rather than narrowing it too quickly.</p>\n"
   ]
  },
